node.text: All hail the proto-athleisure queen Miranda Hobbes, an icon who (rightfully) berated her entire squad for their singular focus on men while simultaneously turning out the fiercest knitwear look south of Houston. (S2/EP1) #MirandaHobbes #Knitwear #Outerwear #Turtleneck #GOAT
He’s younger, he’s hotter, and he’s not the third president in history to be impeached by the House of Representatives! Happy Wednesday, y’all 💋💋

If you’re going to dump a burgeoning real estate tycoon with a raging hard-on for The Rat Pack, do it in this outfit. Because you want him to remember you as Catherine Deneuve on the French Riviera, complete with a fucking hatbox. But the real tragedy of this scene is not the break-up, it’s the fact that we will never get to experience Ms. Bradshaw’s St. Barth’s vacation looks 💔 (S1/EP12) #CarrieBradshaw #Vintage #Midcentury #GloveMoment #Mules #Francophile #Chic

#TBT Miranda by Modigliani 🎨 God bless the insane Sex and the City fans who tag us in photos of this Modigliani painting whenever it is publicly exhibited. Titled “Pierre Edouard Baranowski”, this 1918-era portrait of an androgynous, flame-haired man bears a striking resemblance to a certain corporate lawyer circa season two... #MirandaHobbes #AmedeoModigliani #Androgyny #ArtHistory #Expressionism

ALL ABOUT ANDY 👠Today we’re paying tribute to the man, the myth, the lord of basic cable @bravoandy, who briefly appeared as a shirtless clubgoer in season four AND an unnamed Barneys employee in season six, before his meteoric rise to the top of the Bravo food chain. To borrow terminology from the pop culture Gods @whoweekly, this is quite possibly the most dramatic Who to Them transformation in the history of the series (excluding Lin Manuel Miranda’s blink-or-you’ll-miss-it cameo in the first film). Cohen’s journey from Sex and the City background actor to household name is truly inspirational. Now, if only we could get @candacebushnell on The Real Housewives of New York... (S6/EP14 & S4/EP14 ) #CrucialCameo #AndyCohen

“Hi Oprah, Hi Britney, It’s Kim Cattrall” 🎞 Yes, @kimcattrall played Britney Spears’ mother in Crossroads and yes, her voice is THAT soothing. Put that shit on loop and we can officially retire our rainforest sound machines. RP @jonahtwaterhouse #KimCattrall #Oprah #BritneySpears #TBT
Happy Thanksgiving to everyone except the demon who retouched Kim Cattrall’s face on the Sex and the City 2 poster.

SYDNEY! 🇦🇺 Come celebrate the release of #WeShouldAllBeMirandas at @ourgoldenage on Friday December 13th. Hold onto your cosmos, because for the first time ever we are screening BOTH Sex and the City films! The first film will be presented with a BRAND NEW prerecorded commentary track by Every Outfit’s @chelsea.fairless and @laurengarroni. Tickets can be purchased individually or paired with a signed copy of the book, click the link in our bio for tickets!

SHOPPING IS MY CARDIO 🛍 Our collaborative windows with @decadesinc are up! Major thanks to @cameronsilver, @jeffsnyder1, @ryanatdecades & the whole team. We also want to thank everyone who came out to our launch event last night and @twochickscocktails for the bevs. Fashion credits are as follows...Left to right: Carrie #1: Christian Dior jacket and tank, Eisa petticoat (designed by Cristobal Balenciaga circa ‘53). Carrie #2: Hermés belt. Carrie #3: Moschino jacket, Chanel dress. Charlotte: Alexander McQueen dress, Chanel skirt. Carrie #4: Galitzine dress. Miranda: Versace suit, Junya Watanabe shirt. Samantha: Lolita Lempika suit 💋💋
We’re resurrecting a two-year-old meme because once a Lily Goldenblatt truther, always a Lily Goldenblatt truther.

This isn’t just an outfit, it’s a fucking optical illusion. Someone file a police report, because Samantha’s torso, calves, and thigh are nowhere to be found! We’re impressed that Sam committed to a three-piece set, even if it makes her look like a dismembered news anchor. Say what you want about the questionable use of color-blocking, this woman deserves credit for sheer originality. (S3/EP6) #SamanthaJones #Powersuit #What
Back, by popular demand, an expanded version of the “The Men of Sex and the City as Coffee” series that we posted on stories last week 💋💋

LOS ANGELES! 🌴 Next week we are hosting a VERY fun event with LA’s preeminent vintage emporium @decadesinc! See their new Sex and the City-themed windows (styled by us) and join us for a very special conversation with The Godfather of vintage @cameronsilver. There will be drinks, snacks, and copious amounts of gorgeous clothing. Suggested attire is as follows: giant rosettes, Mugler power suits, Bias-cut Galliano, Burberry dog harnesses, visible bras, Stanford Blatch realness, tutus, bucket hats layered over windbreakers, statement earrings, Prada lipstick prints, Manolo Blahnik mary janes, Aidan Shaw-inspired denim, giant overalls. This event is FREE, to RSVP, e-mail info@decadesinc.com. See you there! 💋💋

#TBT SMITH JERROD...GUCCI MODEL? How did we not know that Jason Lewis appeared in of the most iconic fashion shows of the nineties?  Gucci F/W95 was a satin-heavy, seventies fantasy that established Tom Ford as the go-to man for dangerously low-cut blouses and velvet hiphuggers (a.k.a. the collection that Madonna wore during her altercation with our fave Courtney Love at the ‘95 VMAs, a pop culture moment so major that we have yet to fully recover.) Want more hunky Smith Jerrod modeling moments? See our stories for highlights.

Still obsessed with @bejohnce as Carrie Bradshaw in our 2018 campaign video for @cynthiaenixon 🙏 On a related note, we are VERY excited to be special guests at John’s legendary monthly show at @thesatellitela on November 12th. We will be talking shit about your favorite Sex and the City outfits and hopefully John can be persuaded to reprise his iconic Steve Brady impression. Click the link in our bio for tickets 🚬

THE END OF AN ERA 💧Yesterday, a bankruptcy court judge approved the sale of Barneys New York to Authentic Brands Group for $271.4 million, a move that will likely result in mass store closures. Authentic Brands will then license the Barneys name to other retailers, specifically Saks Fifth Avenue. Which is disheartening, as Barneys’ namesake label has never really wowed us and we have zero desire to set foot in Saks. In the immortal words of Lexy Featherston, is New York (retail) O-V-E-R? (S3/EP7) #CarrieBradshaw #BarneysNewYork #Dior #RIP
